title: If (<-c) is an argument to a function, the whole function evaluates.
pid: 1a998482-b4d3-4593-b260-a60a8ed07c73
body: |2-
  Example: If main's last line is
    ch <- "Bye!"
  and that correspond's to some goroutine's
    fmt.Printf ( <- ch )
  then before main exits,
  the goroutine will print "Bye!"
misc:
- Had_ID_Before_Import
